L2 Regularization¶

$$\text{Loss} = \epsilon^T \epsilon + \lambda \beta^T \beta$$

$ \hat{\beta} = (X^T X + \lambda I)^{-1}X^T y $¶

In [97]:
x, y = generate_data(length=100, seed=42, gaussian_noise=0.1)

DEGREES = np.arange(2, 10)
LAMBDAS = np.logspace(-4, 0, 13)

dd, ll = np.meshgrid(DEGREES, LAMBDAS)

losses = np.zeros((len(LAMBDAS), len(DEGREES)))
for i in range(len(DEGREES)):
    for j in range(len(LAMBDAS)):
        beta = fit_polynomial_regression(x, y, degree=dd[j, i], l=ll[j, i])
        losses[j, i] = mean_square_loss(y, y_hat(x, beta))
    
h = plt.contourf(dd,ll,losses)
plt.colorbar(h)
plt.xlabel('DEGREE')
plt.ylabel('LAMBDA');

Cross Validation¶

Regularization Bayesian Interpretation¶

$$ y_{i}=\mathbf {x} _{i}^{\rm {T}}{\boldsymbol {\beta }}+\varepsilon _{i}, $$

where β is a k × 1 vector, and the ε_i are independent and identically distributed normal random variables:

$$ \varepsilon_{i}\sim N(0,\sigma ^{2}) $$

$ P(y_i | x_i, \sigma, \beta) = \mathcal{N}(y_i - x_i^T \beta; \sigma^2)$¶

$= \exp{\left(-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}(y_i - x_i^T\beta)^2\right)}$¶

$ Likelihood = P(data | model)$¶

$ Likelihood = P(X, Y | \beta, \sigma)$¶

$ Likelihood = P(Y | X, \beta, \sigma) P(X | \beta, \sigma) $¶

Assuming $ P(X | \beta, \sigma) $ is constant, i.e. $X$ does not depend on model parameters

$ Likelihood \propto P(Y | X, \beta, \sigma) $¶

Assuming $\{(x_i, y_i)\}$ pars are independent

$ Likelihood \propto P(y_1, ..., y_N | X, \beta, \sigma) $¶

եթե y-ները իրարից կախված չեն

$ Likelihood \propto \prod_{i=1}^N P(y_i | X, \beta, \sigma) $¶

$ Likelihood \propto \prod_{i=1}^N P(y_i | x_1, .., x_N, \beta, \sigma) $¶

p(y_i| x_j) = p(y_i) if i!= j

$ Likelihood \propto \prod_{i=1}^N P(y_i | x_i, \beta, \sigma) $¶

$ Likelihood \propto \prod_{i=1}^N \mathcal{N}(y_i - x_i^T \beta, \sigma^2)$¶

$ Likelihood \propto \prod_{i=1}^N \exp{\left(-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}(y_i - x_i^T\beta)^2\right)}$¶

$ LogLikelihood \propto -\sum_{i=1}^N \log{\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}} - \sum_{i=1}^N(y_i - x_i^T\beta)^2$¶

Maximum A Posteriori¶

$$ P(model | data) = \frac{P(data | model) P (model)}{P(data)} $$¶

$ Posterior \propto P(Y | X, \beta, \sigma) P(\beta) P(\sigma | \beta) $¶

$P(\sigma | \beta) = P(\sigma)$

$ P(\beta) \propto N(0, \sigma^{'})$

$\lambda = \frac{\sigma}{\sigma^{'}}$

$ LogPosterio \propto -\sigma^{'}\beta \beta^T- \sum_{i=1}^N(y_i - x_i^T\beta)^2$¶
